  "response": "Here are some of the top Perl web application frameworks:\n\n1. Mojolicious\n- Modern, full-featured framework\n- Built-in web server\n- Lightweight and fast\n- Excellent routing\n- Real-time web capabilities\n- Highly recommended for new projects\n\n2. Catalyst\n- Mature and robust framework\n- Model-View-Controller (MVC) architecture\n- Extensive plugin ecosystem\n- Good for large, complex web applications\n- Powerful ORM support\n\n3. Dancer2\n- Lightweight and minimalist\n- Easy to learn\n- Simple routing\n- Modular design\n- Good for small to medium projects\n\n4. Dancer\n- The original version of Dancer\n- Still used, but Dancer2 is recommended for new projects\n\n5. Plack/PSGI\n- Not a full framework, but a standard interface for web applications\n- Allows different web servers and frameworks to work together\n- Provides flexibility and compatibility\n\nRecommendation:\n- For new projects: Mojolicious\n- For enterprise/complex apps: Catalyst\n- For simple/quick apps: Dancer2\n\nThe \"best\" framework depends on your specific project requirements and personal preferences.",
